concat

public Array concat(com.conceptwave.scripting.Object optionalValue)
concat creates a new array consisting of the elements in the this object on which it is called, followed in order by, for each argument, the elements of that argument (if the argument is an array) or the argument itself (if the argument is not an array).

Parameters:
optionalValue - Arrays and/or values to concatenate to the resulting array
Returns:
Returns a new array comprised of this array joined with other array(s) and/or value(s).

sort

public void sort(com.conceptwave.scripting.Object comparator)
Sorts the elements of an array.

Parameters:
comparator - Specified function that defines the sort order. Example 1). sort by their ages (ascending) employees.sort(function(a, b){ return a.age-b.age }) Example 2). sort by employee name employees.sort(function(a, b){ var nameA=a.name.toLowerCase(), nameB=b.name.toLowerCase() if (nameA < nameB) //sort string ascending return -1 if (nameA > nameB) return 1 return 0 //default return value (no sorting) }) Example 3). Sort by birthday employees.sort(function(a, b){ var dateA=new Date(a.birthday), dateB=new Date(b.birthday) return dateA-dateB //sort by date ascending })
